{{Coord|23|29|13|N|120|27|05|E|display=title}} {{Infobox museum | name = Chiayi Municipal Museum | native_name = 嘉義市立博物館 | native_name_lang = zh | logo = | logo_upright = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | image = 嘉義市立博物館.JPG | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | map_type = | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord}} --> | former_name = | established = 9 March 2004 | dissolved = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | location = [[East District, Chiayi City|East]], [[Chiayi City]], [[Taiwan]] | type = [[Museum]] | accreditation = | key_holdings = | collections = | collection_size = | visitors = | founder = | executive_director = | leader_type = | leader = | director = | president = | ceo = | chairperson = | curator = | architect = | historian = | owner = | publictransit = [[Beimen railway station|Beimen Station]] | car_park = | parking = | network = | website = {{URL|http://www.cabcy.gov.tw/cymm/english/new.asp|www.cabcy.gov.tw/cymm}} | embedded = }}
The '''Chiayi Municipal Museum''' ({{zh|c=嘉義市立博物館|p=Jiāyì Shìlì Bówùguǎn}}) is a [[museum]] in [[East District, Chiayi City|East District]], [[Chiayi City]], [[Taiwan]].
==History== The founding of the museum was a collective community effort in the hope to establish a cultural public space for all of the residents of Chiayi City. Among its displays are silk wrappings used to cover [[Tibetan Buddhist]] texts and an [[Islamic]] [[jade]] collection of the [[Qing emperors]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Taiwanese identity: Multiculti roots: A museum tells a new story|url=https://www.economist.com/news/asia/21694576-museum-tells-new-story-multiculti-roots|accessdate=12 March 2016|work=[[The Economist]]|date=12 March 2016}}</ref>
==Exhibitions== The museum has the following galleries:<ref name="taiwan">{{cite web| url=http://eng.taiwan.net.tw/pda/m1.aspx?sNo=0002117&id=5074 | title=Chiayi Municipal Museum | publisher=taiwan.net.tw |location=Taiwan | accessdate=19 January 2014 }}</ref>
* [[Geology|Geological]] Hall * [[Fossil]] Hall * [[Fine Arts]] Gallery
==Activities== The museum offers courses and workshops in calligraphy, brush ink painting, paper mache, illustration, ikebana with a Taiwanese touch etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.culture.tw/index.php?option%3Dcom_sobi2%26sobi2Task%3Dsobi2Details%26sobi2Id%3D654%26Itemid%3D175 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-11-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141103092121/http://www.culture.tw/index.php?option=com_sobi2&sobi2Task=sobi2Details&sobi2Id=654&Itemid=175 |archivedate=2014-11-03 |df= }}</ref>
==Transportation== The museum is accessible within walking distance west from [[Beimen railway station|Beimen Station]] of the [[Alishan Forest Railway]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cabcy.gov.tw/cymm/english/traffic.asp |title=Chia-Yi Municipal Museum |publisher=Cabcy.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-04-21}}</ref>
