{{other uses|Loudspeaker (disambiguation)}}
{{Infobox play | name = Loud Speaker | image = | image_size = | caption = | writer = [[John Howard Lawson]] | chorus = | characters = | mute = | setting = | premiere = {{Start date|1927|03|02|mf=yes}} | place = [[New Playwrights' Theatre]] | orig_lang = [[English language|English]] | series = | subject = | genre = [[Modernism|Modernist]] [[farce]] | web = }} '''''Loud Speaker''''' is a play by American playwright [[John Howard Lawson]]. It was first produced by the New Playwrights' Theatre at the [[52nd Street Theatre]] in [[New York City|New York]], opening on March 2 [[1927 in literature#New drama|1927]]. [[Harry Wagstaff Gribble]] directed, [[Mordecai Gorelik]] [[Scenography|designed the sets]], [[Eugene L. Berton]] composed its music, and [[Leonard Sillman]] choreographed its dances.
